    "summary": "I have gained extensive experience in Electron Microscopy, especially in development of detectors and advanced methods for Semiconductor and Material Science.\nI enjoy both software and hardware development and enjoy leading projects by example and by adopting an agile approach. I am a person who works hard and generates lots of ideas and enthusiasm.\n\nSpecialties: Advanced Technology Development, Intellectual Property, Innovation Strategy, Electron Microscopy.\n\nCompetences and Skills:\n- Proven experience interacting with customers and anticipating their long-term needs\n- Proven experience leading team with a strong focus on both people and content\n- Strong written, verbal and presentation skills to report results out to multiple levels of business leadership and provide recommendations for further action \n- Strong collaboration and networking skills both internal and external.\n- Strong business acumen and or ability to present to executive leadership.\n- Advanced understanding of material science, physics, and engineering.\n- Broad experience with electron microscopes and similar analytical instrumentation. \n- Very strong expertise in detection space\n- Ability to travel to conferences, customers, or other sites, including international.\n- Ability to understand, anticipate, and propose resolutions to customer challenges on engineering and scientific subject areas.\n\n- Lead a team of scientists to craft, develop and prototype solutions to innovative technical challenges relevant to customer base and aligned with a business plan. Ability to hold both individuals and team accountable to set and deliver on quarterly expectations.\n\n- Identify and collaborate regularly with customers, key opinion leaders, and global business unit partners to define and execute on project ideas and scopes.\n\n- Analyze, evaluate and report on new technologies with recommendations to the business on action plans including make, buy or partner. \n\n- Evaluate current business processes and systems. Plan and implement procedures and system to improve innovation and efficiency. Hold the team accountable for measurable improvements. \n\n- Drive strategic innovation by supporting new idea conception as well as increasing new patent filings. Hold team accountable for annual improvements in patent filings.\n\nKind regards,\n\nStefano Vespucci",
